<subSubSection pageId="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1124,1149]" pageId="9">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male genitalia are very similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[749,944,1124,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Brachiacantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bistripustulata">
<emphasis box="[749,944,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="9">B. bistripustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genitalia, but the cusps on the third ventrite of male are narrower in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nestor-Arriola &amp; Toledo-Hernández" authorityYear="2017" box="[435,630,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Brachiacantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustihamata">
<emphasis box="[435,630,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="9">B. robustihamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The cusps on the third male ventrite of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nestor-Arriola &amp; Toledo-Hernández" authorityYear="2017" box="[1110,1272,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Brachiacantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustihamata">
<emphasis box="[1110,1272,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="9">robustihamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar in shape to the cusps of 
<taxonomicName authority="Nunenmacher" authorityName="Nunenmacher" authorityYear="1909" box="[401,706,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Brachiacantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blaisdelli">
<emphasis box="[401,538,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="9">B. blaisdelli</emphasis>
Nunenmacher
</taxonomicName>
, but the apical hook of the male genitalia is bigger and rounder than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunenmacher" authorityYear="1909" box="[235,339,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Brachiacantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blaisdelli">
<emphasis box="[235,339,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="9">blaisdelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1268,1293]" pageId="9">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Latin “robust” and “hamatus”. The name refers size of the apical hook of the basal lobe of male genitalia.
</paragraph>
